  <subsection xml:id="subsec-secant-function">
    <title>The Secant Function</title>
    <p>
      As discussed earlier in this section, the secant function has a domain for all real numbers except angles of <m>n\frac{\pi}{2}</m>, where <m>n</m> is an integer. These excluded values correspond to the vertical asymptotes of the secant function. With a period of <m>2\pi</m>, we can focus on the interval <m>0</m> to <m>2\pi</m>. The construction of the secant function plot follows a similar approach to that used for the cosecant function, as illustrated in <xref ref="secant-graph-animation"/>.
    </p>
